```

So we have $\sum_i \varepsilon \cdot |(\partial_i f)(x)| = \varepsilon \cdot \sum_i |(\partial_i f)(x)|$.

Now, we can combine the inequalities:

$|g'(0)| \leq \sum_i |(y_i - x_i) \cdot (\partial_i f)(x)| \leq \sum_i \varepsilon \cdot |(\partial_i f)(x)| = \varepsilon \cdot \sum_i |(\partial_i f)(x)|$.

Let's complete the formal proof:

```tactics
linarith [h2, h3, h4]
```

This completes the proof that $|g'(0)| \leq \varepsilon \cdot \sum_i |(\partial_i f)(x)|$.

